{0 day11-opam-build}

Opam package build orchestration: compiles packages inside layered
containers and manages the build cache. {!Day11_opam_build.Build_layer} handles the
single-layer container lifecycle — locking, overlay mounting, runc
invocation, cleanup, and sidecar writing. {!Day11_opam_build.Dag} constructs
deduplicated DAGs of build nodes across multiple solver solutions.
{!Day11_opam_build.Dag_executor} runs the DAG in parallel using Eio fibers with
promise-based memoization, skipping cached nodes. {!Day11_opam_build.Hash_cache}
memoizes content-hash computation for layer cache keys. {!Day11_opam_build.Tools}
solves and builds tool packages (odoc, sherlodoc, etc.) from pinned
local checkouts or the opam repository. {!Day11_opam_build.Types} defines shared build
types: {!Day11_opam_build.Types.build_env}, {!Day11_opam_build.Types.build_result}, and
{!Day11_opam_build.Types.build_strategy}. {!Day11_opam_build.Base} manages base image layers (Docker
import and caching). {!Day11_opam_build.Debug} provides interactive debug containers
for investigating failed builds. {!Day11_opam_build.Patches} manages per-package patch
files that modify builds before execution.

Depends on {!day11-runner}, {!day11-opam-layer}, {!day11-solver} (via
solver_pool), {!day11-opam}, {!page-solution}, and the lower layer and
container libraries.

